<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Lady Amelia Windsor has shared a series of throwback photographs to mark her elder sister Lady Marina's 28th birthday in a gushing tribute to the royal. </p>

<p>Amelia, 25, who is 39th in line to the throne, is seen exploring a garden alongside her sister and brother Edward Downpatrick, 31, as youngsters in one of the adorable snaps, while another captures the two women giggling together on a sofa.</p>

<p>Lady Amelia shared the pictures to Instagram, with the caption: 'My world, I love you to the moon and stars. Happy, happy birthday you bizarre, beautiful and brillIant buffoon.'</p>

<p>An appreciative Marina was quick to reply with her own sweet message, commenting on her sister's post: 'Love you so much my beautiful angel magical Mel.' </p>

<p>Lady Amelia Windsor. 25. shared a series of throwback photographs to mark her elder sister Lady Marina's 28th birthday in a gushing tribute to the royal (pictured, the sisters alongside their brother Edward Downpatrick, 31, </p>

<p>The royal posted a host of family snaps alongside her lookalike sister from over the years, including one as they shared a laugh relaxing on a sofa together </p>

<p>The heiress and model, who turned 25 earlier this month and is the granddaughter of the Duke of Kent, has returned to Notting Hill, London, after spending lockdown at her parents' Cambridge property.</p>

<p>Lady Amelia's elder sister Marina, who attends Cambridge university, also appeared to stay at the family estate amid the coronavirus pandemic.</p>

<p>Amelia has modelled for the likes of Dolce &amp; Gabbana and designed her own range of accessories in collaboration with Penelope Chilvers. </p>

<p>She is represented by Storm models, which also looks after the likes of Kate Moss and Cara Delevingne.</p>

<p>Lady Amelia shared the pictures to Instagram in a gushing tribute on Instagram, calling Marina 'my world'</p>

<p>Sister selfies! The royal, who is 39th in line to the throne, called her sister a 'bizarre, beautiful and brillIant baffoon' in the personal post </p>

<p>Additionally she has been named as a contributing editor in Tatler Magazine, and reportedly interned at jewellery house Bulgari, during her time studying at Edinburgh university.</p>

<p>Despite most of the royals keeping their private life off social media, Amelia is a big fan of Instagram and regularly shares glimpses of her glamorous life with her 84,700 followers.</p>

<p>Her sister Marina also has a public social media account, with nearly 4,000 followers, and often shares photographs of her stunning family.</p>

<p>Despite backlash over Londoners escaping to visit their second homes at the start of the UK's coronavirus-related lockdown, Lady Amelia fled to her parents' home in Cambridge in late March. Pictured: A snap of the area, shared by the royal to her Instagram in April </p>

<p>Amelia has previously suggested that her Instagram account is just a snapshot of her life, with the eco-friendly royal revealing that she tries to live as sustainably as possible and often borrows clothes from brands for events.</p>

<p>The royal fled to her parents' house in Cambridge in late March, joining the Londoners escaping to visit their second homes at the start of the UK's coronavirus-related lockdown.</p>

<p>She shared a snap of the city dated 23 March, a week after the government advised against all non-essential travel and fears mounted that capital dwellers could be spreading the disease across the country.</p>
